text: Jacqui Stewart (nee Apiata, born 10 June 1966) was a New Zealand rugby union player. She played for the New Zealand women's national rugby union team at the 1991 Women's Rugby World Cup. She grew up in Otautau. She studied at Central Southland College, and University of Canterbury. == References == Category:1966 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand rugby union players
